## Overview

This document defines standards for developing REST APIs at La Nación using the `LaNacion.Core.Templates.Web.Api.Minimal` template. The architecture follows Clean Architecture principles with CQRS pattern, event-driven design, and strict separation of concerns.

## Technology Stack

### Core Technologies
- **.NET 6**: Runtime and framework
- **C#**: Primary programming language
- **ASP.NET Core Minimal APIs**: Web framework
- **MediatR**: CQRS mediator pattern implementation
- **Dapper**: Micro-ORM for database access
- **FluentValidation**: Input validation

### Database & Data Access
- **MySQL**: Primary database (also supports SQL Server, PostgreSQL)
- **Dapper**: Lightweight ORM with raw SQL
- **Unit of Work**: Transaction management via `LaNacion.Core.Infraestructure.Data.Relational`

### Messaging & Events
- **AWS SQS**: Message queuing
- **AWS EventBridge**: Event routing
- **Outbox Pattern**: Transactional event publishing

### Testing & Quality
- **xUnit**: Testing framework
- **Moq**: Mocking library
- **FluentAssertions**: Assertion library

### Infrastructure
- **Serilog**: Structured logging
- **AWS Secrets Manager**: Configuration management
- **AutoMapper**: Object mapping
- **System.ServiceModel**: WCF client integration (legacy)

## Architecture Overview

### Clean Architecture with CQRS

The API follows Clean Architecture with vertical slicing through CQRS:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         Presentation Layer                  │
│  (Minimal API Endpoints, Controllers)       │
└──────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
               │
┌──────────────▼──────────────────────────────┐
│         Application Layer                   │
│  (Commands, Queries, Handlers, Validators)  │
└──────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
               │
┌──────────────▼──────────────────────────────┐
│         Domain Layer                        │
│  (Entities, Value Objects, Interfaces)      │
└──────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
               │
┌──────────────▼──────────────────────────────┐
│         Infrastructure Layer                │
│  (Repositories, External Services, DB)      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Project Structure

```
LaNacion.Suscripciones.Api/
├── LaNacion.Suscripciones.Domain/
│   ├── Entities/              # Domain entities
│   └── Events/                # Domain events
├── LaNacion.Suscripciones.Application/
│   ├── Commands/              # Write operations
│   ├── Queries/               # Read operations
│   ├── Handlers/              # MediatR handlers
│   └── Validators/            # FluentValidation
├── LaNacion.Suscripciones.Application.Interfaces/
│   └── Persistance/           # Repository interfaces
├── LaNacion.Suscripciones.Repositories.SQL/
│   └── Implementations/       # Dapper repositories
├── LaNacion.Suscripciones.Services/
│   └── Adapters/              # WCF/External service adapters
└── LaNacion.Suscripciones.Api/
    ├── Endpoints/             # Minimal API endpoint definitions
    ├── Program.cs             # Application entry point
    └── appsettings.json       # Configuration
```

## Domain-Driven Design Principles

### Entities

Entities have unique identifiers and encapsulate business logic.

```csharp
public class Suscripcion
{
    public Guid Id { get; set; }
    public string ClienteId { get; set; }
    public string PlanId { get; set; }
    public DateTime FechaInicio { get; set; }
    public EstadoSuscripcion Estado { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public string CreatedBy { get; set; }
    
    public void Activar()
    {
        if (Estado != EstadoSuscripcion.Pendiente)
            throw new InvalidOperationException("Solo se pueden activar suscripciones pendientes");
            
        Estado = EstadoSuscripcion.Activa;
    }
}
```

### Value Objects

Value objects are immutable and defined by their attributes.

```csharp
public record DireccionEntrega
{
    public string Calle { get; init; }
    public string Numero { get; init; }
    public string CodigoPostal { get; init; }
    public string Ciudad { get; init; }
    
    public DireccionEntrega(string calle, string numero, string codigoPostal, string ciudad)
    {
        if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(calle))
            throw new ArgumentException("Calle es requerida", nameof(calle));
            
        Calle = calle;
        Numero = numero;
        CodigoPostal = codigoPostal;
        Ciudad = ciudad;
    }
}
```

### Aggregates

Aggregates maintain consistency boundaries.

```csharp
public class Suscripcion // Aggregate Root
{
    public Guid Id { get; set; }
    public List<Producto> Productos { get; private set; } = new();
    
    public void AgregarProducto(Producto producto)
    {
        if (Productos.Any(p => p.Id == producto.Id))
            throw new InvalidOperationException("Producto ya existe en la suscripción");
            
        Productos.Add(producto);
    }
}
```

### Repositories

Repository interfaces define data access contracts.

```csharp
// Domain layer - Interface
public interface ISuscripcionRepository : IRepository<Suscripcion, Guid>
{
    Task<Suscripcion> GetByClienteIdAsync(string clienteId);
    Task<List<Suscripcion>> GetActivasAsync();
}

// Infrastructure layer - Implementation
public class SuscripcionRepository : BaseRepository<Suscripcion, Guid>, ISuscripcionRepository
{
    public SuscripcionRepository(IContext context) : base(context, "Suscripciones") { }
    
    public async Task<Suscripcion> GetByClienteIdAsync(string clienteId)
    {
        const string sql = "SELECT * FROM Suscripciones WHERE ClienteId = @ClienteId";
        return await _context.Connection.QueryFirstOrDefaultAsync<Suscripcion>(
            sql, 
            new { ClienteId = clienteId }, 
            Transaction
        );
    }
}
```

## SOLID Principles

### Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)

Each class has one reason to change.

```csharp
// Good: Separated concerns
public class Suscripcion
{
    public void Activar() { /* business logic */ }
}

public class SuscripcionRepository
{
    public async Task SaveAsync(Suscripcion suscripcion) { /* persistence */ }
}

public class SuscripcionValidator : AbstractValidator<CreateSuscripcionCommand>
{
    public SuscripcionValidator() { /* validation rules */ }
}
```

### Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP)

Depend on abstractions, not concretions.

```csharp
// Good: Depends on interface
public class CreateSuscripcionHandler : IRequestHandler<CreateSuscripcionCommand, Guid>
{
    private readonly ISuscripcionRepository _repository;
    private readonly IUnitOfWork _uow;
    
    public CreateSuscripcionHandler(ISuscripcionRepository repository, IUnitOfWork uow)
    {
        _repository = repository;
        _uow = uow;
    }
}
```

## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

**Classes and Interfaces:**
```csharp
public class SuscripcionService { }           // PascalCase
public interface ISuscripcionRepository { }   // PascalCase with I prefix
```

**Methods and Properties:**
```csharp
public async Task<Suscripcion> GetByIdAsync(Guid id) { }  // PascalCase
public string ClienteId { get; set; }                      // PascalCase
```

**Variables and Parameters:**
```csharp
var suscripcionId = Guid.NewGuid();  // camelCase
public void Process(string clienteId) { }
```

**Constants:**
```csharp
private const int MAX_PRODUCTOS_POR_SUSCRIPCION = 10;  // UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
```

### Command Naming Convention

Commands follow the pattern: `cmd-{verb}-{entity}`

```csharp
// Command class name
public record CreateSuscripcionCommand : IRequest<Guid>
{
    public string ClienteId { get; init; }
    public string PlanId { get; init; }
}

// Conceptual command name for logging/events
// "cmd-crear-suscripcion"
```

### Event Naming Convention

Events follow the pattern: `evt-{squad}-{entity}-{verb-past}`

```csharp
// Event class name
public class SuscripcionCreada : INotification
{
    public Guid SuscripcionId { get; set; }
    public string ClienteId { get; set; }
    public DateTime OccurredOnUtc { get; set; }
}

// Event name for EventBridge
// "evt-susc-suscripcion-creada"
```

### Language Requirements

All code, comments, and messages MUST be in English:

```csharp
// Good
throw new NotFoundException("Subscription not found");
_logger.LogInformation("Processing subscription creation");

// Avoid
throw new NotFoundException("Suscripción no encontrada");
_logger.LogInformation("Procesando creación de suscripción");
```

## CQRS Implementation

### Commands (Write Operations)

```csharp
// Command
public record CreateSuscripcionCommand : IRequest<Guid>
{
    public string ClienteId { get; init; }
    public string PlanId { get; init; }
    public List<string> ProductoIds { get; init; }
}

// Validator
public class CreateSuscripcionCommandValidator : AbstractValidator<CreateSuscripcionCommand>
{
    public CreateSuscripcionCommandValidator()
    {
        RuleFor(x => x.ClienteId).NotEmpty().MaximumLength(50);
        RuleFor(x => x.PlanId).NotEmpty();
        RuleFor(x => x.ProductoIds).NotEmpty();
    }
}

// Handler
public class CreateSuscripcionHandler : IRequestHandler<CreateSuscripcionCommand, Guid>
{
    private readonly ISuscripcionRepository _repository;
    private readonly IUnitOfWork _uow;
    private readonly IMessagePublisher _publisher;
    
    public CreateSuscripcionHandler(
        ISuscripcionRepository repository,
        IUnitOfWork uow,
        IMessagePublisher publisher)
    {
        _repository = repository;
        _uow = uow;
        _publisher = publisher;
    }
    
    public async Task<Guid> Handle(CreateSuscripcionCommand command, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        using (_uow.BeginTransaction())
        {
            var suscripcion = new Suscripcion
            {
                Id = Guid.NewGuid(),
                ClienteId = command.ClienteId,
                PlanId = command.PlanId,
                Estado = EstadoSuscripcion.Pendiente,
                CreatedAt = DateTime.UtcNow
            };
            
            await _repository.AddAsync(suscripcion);
            
            // Publish event inside transaction (Outbox Pattern)
            await _publisher.CreateMessageAsync(
                "evt-susc-suscripcion-creada",
                new SuscripcionCreadaEvent
                {
                    SuscripcionId = suscripcion.Id,
                    ClienteId = suscripcion.ClienteId,
                    OccurredOnUtc = DateTime.UtcNow
                }
            );
            
            _uow.Commit();
            return suscripcion.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

### Queries (Read Operations)

```csharp
// Query
public record GetSuscripcionByIdQuery : IRequest<SuscripcionDto>
{
    public Guid Id { get; init; }
}

// Handler
public class GetSuscripcionByIdHandler : IRequestHandler<GetSuscripcionByIdQuery, SuscripcionDto>
{
    private readonly ISuscripcionRepository _repository;
    
    public GetSuscripcionByIdHandler(ISuscripcionRepository repository)
    {
        _repository = repository;
    }
    
    public async Task<SuscripcionDto> Handle(GetSuscripcionByIdQuery query, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        var suscripcion = await _repository.GetByIdAsync(query.Id);
        
        if (suscripcion == null)
            throw new NotFoundException($"Subscription {query.Id} not found");
            
        return new SuscripcionDto
        {
            Id = suscripcion.Id,
            ClienteId = suscripcion.ClienteId,
            Estado = suscripcion.Estado.ToString()
        };
    }
}
```

## API Design Standards

### REST Endpoint Naming

Follow REST conventions with plural nouns and kebab-case:

```csharp
// Good: Plural nouns, no verbs
app.MapPost("/api/v1/suscripciones", CreateSuscripcion);
app.MapGet("/api/v1/suscripciones/{id}", GetSuscripcion);
app.MapPut("/api/v1/suscripciones/{id}", UpdateSuscripcion);
app.MapDelete("/api/v1/suscripciones/{id}", DeleteSuscripcion);
app.MapGet("/api/v1/suscripciones/{id}/productos", GetProductos);

// Avoid: Verbs in URLs
app.MapPost("/api/v1/crear-suscripcion", ...);  // ❌
app.MapGet("/api/v1/obtener-suscripcion/{id}", ...);  // ❌
```

### Endpoint Implementation

```csharp
public class SuscripcionEndpoints : IEndpointDefinition
{
    public void DefineEndpoints(WebApplication app)
    {
        app.MapPost("/api/v1/suscripciones", CreateSuscripcion)
            .WithName("CreateSuscripcion")
            .WithTags("Suscripciones")
            .Produces<Guid>(StatusCodes.Status201Created)
            .ProducesValidationProblem();
    }
    
    private static async Task<IResult> CreateSuscripcion(
        CreateSuscripcionCommand command,
        IMediator mediator)
    {
        var id = await mediator.Send(command);
        return Results.Created($"/api/v1/suscripciones/{id}", new { id });
    }
}
```

### HTTP Status Codes

```csharp
// 200 OK - Successful GET/PUT
return Results.Ok(suscripcion);

// 201 Created - Successful POST
return Results.Created($"/api/v1/suscripciones/{id}", new { id });

// 204 No Content - Successful DELETE
return Results.NoContent();

// 400 Bad Request - Validation error
return Results.BadRequest(new { error = "Invalid data" });

// 404 Not Found - Resource not found
return Results.NotFound(new { error = "Subscription not found" });

// 500 Internal Server Error - Unhandled exception
return Results.Problem("An error occurred");
```

