## Event Publishing Patterns

### Outbox Pattern

Events are published inside the same transaction as entity changes:

```csharp
public async Task<Guid> Handle(CreateSuscripcionCommand command, CancellationToken ct)
{
    using (_uow.BeginTransaction())
    {
        // 1. Persist entity
        await _repository.AddAsync(suscripcion);
        
        // 2. Publish event (stored in Outbox table)
        await _publisher.CreateMessageAsync(
            "evt-susc-suscripcion-creada",
            new SuscripcionCreadaEvent { ... }
        );
        
        // 3. Commit transaction (both entity and event)
        _uow.Commit();
    }
}
```

### Event Structure

```csharp
public class SuscripcionCreadaEvent
{
    public Guid SuscripcionId { get; set; }
    public string ClienteId { get; set; }
    public string PlanId { get; set; }
    public DateTime OccurredOnUtc { get; set; }
}
```

### EventBridge Integration

Events are routed through EventBridge with detail-type:

```json
{
  "DetailType": "VentasAlta",
  "Source": "suscripciones-api",
  "EventBusName": "suscripciones-prod-eventbridge-main",
  "Detail": {
    "eventName": "evt-susc-suscripcion-creada",
    "subscriptionId": "sub-123",
    "customerId": "cust-456",
    "occurredOnUtc": "2026-01-22T10:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

## Database Patterns

### Dapper with Unit of Work

```csharp
public class SuscripcionRepository : BaseRepository<Suscripcion, Guid>, ISuscripcionRepository
{
    public SuscripcionRepository(IContext context) : base(context, "Suscripciones") { }
    
    public override async Task<Guid> AddAsync(Suscripcion entity, CancellationToken ct = default)
    {
        const string sql = @"
            INSERT INTO Suscripciones(Id, ClienteId, PlanId, Estado, CreatedAt)
            VALUES (@Id, @ClienteId, @PlanId, @Estado, @CreatedAt)";
            
        await _context.Connection.ExecuteAsync(sql, entity, Transaction);
        return entity.Id;
    }
    
    public async Task<Suscripcion> GetByIdAsync(Guid id)
    {
        const string sql = "SELECT * FROM Suscripciones WHERE Id = @Id";
        return await _context.Connection.QueryFirstOrDefaultAsync<Suscripcion>(
            sql,
            new { Id = id },
            Transaction
        );
    }
}
```

### Transaction Management

```csharp
// Always use Unit of Work for transactions
using (_uow.BeginTransaction())
{
    await _repository.AddAsync(entity);
    await _publisher.CreateMessageAsync("event-name", eventData);
    _uow.Commit();
}
```

### Dependency Injection

```csharp
// Program.cs or Extensions
services.AddScoped<ISuscripcionRepository, SuscripcionRepository>();
services.AddScoped<IUnitOfWork, UnitOfWork>();
```

