## Performance Best Practices

### Async/Await

Always use async/await for I/O operations:

```csharp
// Good
public async Task<Suscripcion> GetByIdAsync(Guid id)
{
    return await _repository.GetByIdAsync(id);
}

// Avoid blocking calls
public Suscripcion GetById(Guid id)
{
    return _repository.GetByIdAsync(id).Result;  // ❌
}
```

### Database Query Optimization

```csharp
// Good: Select only needed fields
const string sql = "SELECT Id, ClienteId, Estado FROM Suscripciones WHERE Id = @Id";

// Avoid: Select all fields when not needed
const string sql = "SELECT * FROM Suscripciones WHERE Id = @Id";  // ❌
```

## Security Best Practices

### Input Validation

Always validate inputs with FluentValidation:

```csharp
public class CreateSuscripcionCommandValidator : AbstractValidator<CreateSuscripcionCommand>
{
    public CreateSuscripcionCommandValidator()
    {
        RuleFor(x => x.ClienteId)
            .NotEmpty()
            .MaximumLength(50)
            .Matches("^[A-Z0-9-]+$");
    }
}
```

### Secrets Management

Never hardcode credentials:

```csharp
// Good: Use AWS Secrets Manager or User Secrets
var connectionString = configuration["ConnectionStrings:Default"];

// Avoid: Hardcoded credentials
var connectionString = "Server=localhost;Database=db;User=admin;Password=123";  // ❌
```

